        "strings" : {
          "title" : "Telos: Distress Call",
          "varaName" : "Dart"
        },
        "stages" : {
          "destroyFleet" : {
            "intel" : {
              "subtitle" : "Destroy the $f:pirates{pirate} fleet",
              "desc" : "Karengo's distress signal claims that he has discovered something hidden, but he is stranded on-world.\nDestroy the $f:pirates{pirate} fleet around ${telosPt1Stg1DestPlanet} in ${telosPt1Stg1DestSystem}."
            }
          },
          "landOnPlanetFirst" : {
            "intel" : {
              "subtitle" : "Rendezvous with Karengo",
              "desc" : "Land on ${telosPt1Stg1DestPlanet} in ${telosPt1Stg1DestSystem} to see what Karengo has discovered."
            },
            "pages" : [ {
              "id" : "1",
              "paras" : [ "Your shuttle traces an arc down to the planet’s surface, following the pulse of the distress signal. Surface scans reveal the overgrown ruins of a colony and evidence of orbital bombardment, though nothing is recorded in the - admittedly unreliable - fleet datastore.", "As you step outside, still pondering the ruins, your thoughts are interrupted by Karengo himself, striding purposefully toward the cooling shuttle in his weathered duster - confirming the ship instruments’ classification of the atmosphere as “env-suit optional.”" ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "1.5"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "1.5",
              "paras" : [ "“Well now, is that Captain ${playerLastName}?” he asks with a touch of incredulity, “Didn't expect to see my best pilot-for-hire out here. Great job on those bounty hunters. Dumb as holovids, but well armed. Now come on, follow me and you'll see why I'm here.”" ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "1.5-1"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "1.5-1",
              "paras" : [ "Bending over a large metal slab, he runs his glove along the side until there's an audible click and, with a rumble you can feel through the blasted soil, it slides open to reveal a narrow staircase lit by gentle blue emergency lighting.", "A memory surfaces, unbidden, of diving below the waves on your previous adventure with the man. You start down the stairs." ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "1.6"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "1.6",
              "paras" : [ "At last, the corridor levels out and flares into a small amphitheater. Low, padded benches are arranged in a scattered circle. A blue crest hangs at the far end, with the word ‘TELOS’ embossed beneath. The room is minimally decorated, even accounting for the seismic devastation from the bombardment. Sheaves of paper, music stands and paintings of paradise worlds litter the cracked floor.", "Splayed across the benches are a dozen desiccated bodies. Even in death, they are holding hands, as if in silent prayer." ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "2"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "2",
              "paras" : [ "Karengo sweeps past the scene to a door on the far side and steps through. \"Here's what we came for!\" he calls. Stepping back out, he hands you one of two capped syringes, the contents gray.", "\"It's Ether,\" he says. \"One shot o’this, and your mind will be expanded. I’m talking telepathy, mind meld, telekinesis, remote vision…it's taken months to track down this site, and this vial’s for you as my thanks for the lift.\"" ],
              "onPageShown" : {
                "goToPage" : "3"
              }
            }, {
              "id" : "3",
              "options" : [ {
                "id" : "requestMoreInfo",
                "text" : "“I'm gonna need to know a lot more.”",
                "goToPage" : "5"
              }, {
                "id" : "afterYou",
                "text" : "“Right after you.”",
                "goToPage" : "4"
              }, {
                "id" : "noInject",
                "text" : "==Wait until later==",
                "tooltip" : "This choice will not affect quest rewards.",
                "goToPage" : "12"
              }, {
                "id" : "injectSelf",
                "text" : "==Inject yourself==",
                "tooltip" : "This choice will not affect quest rewards.",
                "goToPage" : "7"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "4",
              "paras" : [ "Karengo laughs. “Let’s each hold onto these for now then, yeah? They seem to keep well, so we can use ‘em any time.”" ],
              "onPageShown" : {
                "goToPage" : "3"
              }
            }, {
              "id" : "5",
              "paras" : [ "Karengo lowers his voice theatrically and glances around, as if ensuring there are no eavesdroppers.", "“My source says this here was a ==Telos== base.”", "At your blank look, he continues. “Telos…one of the old Tri-Tachyon research branches the Hegemony erased. They created this Ether goo” - he taps a finger against the gray tube - “then left to live out away from the Core Worlds. And then the Hegemony hunted ‘em down and purged ‘em from history. Gone.”" ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "\"But, why?\"",
                "goToPage" : "6"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "6",
              "paras" : [ "“Because this goo is nanites,” he says. “An’ after the First AI War, do you think the Big Hedge were gonna let a bunch of scientists run off with nanotech? Not a chance. They killed ‘em all, then covered up the whole mess.” He straightens a little. “Least, that’s what my source says.”", "“So…ready to try it out?”" ],
              "onPageShown" : {
                "goToPage" : "3"
              }
            }, {
              "id" : "7",
              "paras" : [ "You sink the plunger deep into your right leg. The gray liquid drains from the barrel and you feel a wave of cold spreading from the site. Karengo watches intently, uncharacteristically quiet, as you take a seat on a stair and wait.", "You black out." ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "8"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "8",
              "paras" : [ "Consciousness returns unwillingly. Your head reverberates with unfamiliar awareness; just as you always know, without looking, where your bridge crew is while in flight, you are inexplicably aware that you’re in the chapel. The power station is offline, but the backup battery supplying power to the hanger tunnel door is- " ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "8.1"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "8.1",
              "paras" : [ "With effort, you crack your eyes open. Karengo is pacing restlessly at the far end of the chapel, picking up and then tossing detritus at the wall - dead TriPads, wall ornaments, small sculptures - possibly searching for secret doors and possibly just killing time.", "At your thought, the reinforced slab below the rich throw rug under a wrecked bench whirs, then starts to grind open. Karengo’s arm freezes mid-throw.", "In the sudden stillness of the chamber, the new sound reverberates. Karengo looks down, then at the spot on the wall where he’d shattered a porcelain figurine moments before, and finally at you." ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Ask what happened",
                "goToPage" : "9"
              }, {
                "text" : "Play it cool",
                "goToPage" : "10"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "9",
              "paras" : [ "“Did, uh, you did that, right?” you ask woozily. “Because if not…” you trail off.", "Karengo shakes his head and points at the porcelain shards. “Unless they broke one of these each time they want to open a door, nah. Wasn’t me.”" ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "11"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "10",
              "paras" : [ "You shrug casually at Karengo’s confusion. For the first time since you met, you’re a step ahead of the adventurer. You take a moment to savor it." ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "11"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "11",
              "paras" : [ "“That was you,” he says finally. “I didn’t think- I mean, it actually worked.”", "This is the first time he has expressed anything but confidence in the safety of the nanite injection, but it’s difficult to feel betrayed with the stairs down to the hanger wide open, the lone ship there sleeping, waiting to be woken again. Even after so many cycles, it hums with stored energy, and you slip into it. Fractured silicates coat your-its hull, knocked loose by the bombardment, pebbles and dust gathering in divots along the sleek, smooth exterior like vernal pools. You could effortlessly bring the entire system online, shaking free the rubble to soar again. A thought reaches out to-" ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "11.1"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "11.1",
              "paras" : [ "Karengo is shaking you and, despite the beckoning trapdoor leading to the ship, you find yourself dazedly led back to your shuttle and whisked into orbit. Exploration takes a back seat as the medical team prepares a dizzying array of tests to run on you, which they promise will be “quick and next to painless”.", "You find yourself with little choice but to wait until the medics are done before returning planetside." ],
              "options" : [ {
                "id" : "leave",
                "text" : "Leave"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "12",
              "paras" : [ "Karengo tucks his syringe of Ether into one of the endless pockets in his tactical jacket and you follow suit, the cylinder pressing against your ribs. “According to my contact,” he says, glancing around, “there is tunnel access to a hanger from this room.” At your raised eyebrows, he adds, “Somewhere.”" ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "12.1"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "12.1",
              "paras" : [ "After an extended search, during which more than a few things are shattered “to see if there’s a key or somethin’ inside”, Karengo pulls a rug away from an overturned bench, exposing a metal panel. The long scrapes give it away as a sliding trapdoor, but there is no unlock mechanism in sight, kicking off another long period of fruitless searching." ],
              "options" : [ {
                "text" : "Continue",
                "goToPage" : "12.2"
              } ]
            }, {
              "id" : "12.2",
              "paras" : [ "In the end, the two of you decide to let the experts tackle the problem. Over Karengo’s guarantees that the base is not ‘booby-trapped’, your head of security whisks you up to the relative safety of orbit as engineers crawl over the room, searching for entry. “Won’t take long, sir,” the head of engineering sounds apologetic. “Just give us a day here and it’ll be open when you return.”" ],
              "options" : [ {
                "id" : "leave",
                "text" : "Leave"
              } ]
            } ]
          },
